reviews.text: Phenomenal from the appetizer to the main course. Family style restaurant - order it all and fork(sword) fight over the delicious selections. We had a little bit of everything and was not disappointed. Very attentive staff. Popular place in town will get full so plan accordingly!

Our dinner was great! The six of us all loved our food, shares, sides.  Sunset was lovely and one of few places you can see it.  Only downside is making reservations is difficult.  No one ever answers the phone & the app declines all reservations for 6 or more,  makes you go to waiting list then approves you later when it was always available. I'm sure they are losing business due to lack of human answering.

What a terrific restaurant. My party of three tried appetizers,  a different entree each and then, because everyone raved about the appetizers and entrees,  we ordered a dessert that was large enough to split three ways. We rarely order dessert. This is a BYOB place and had we known,  would have brought a bottle of wine. Don't miss this place.

Great ambience, wonderful service, but some of our food literally was inedible- loaded with salt!  And this is from someone who loves potato chips.  We could not eat our flounder because it was so salty.  We sent it back and lo and behold - we got the same fish back again, as salty as ever, and recooked - the edges were browned.  We had no choice but to send it back again - really irritated this time.  We overhead a person at the next table commenting on his fish being too salty.   And the calamari was full of salt, too.
There was something wrong in this kitchen in mid-August.  And I wouldn't recommend the place  - they just didn't rectify the situation promptly and correctly.

Great food and atmosphere.  Attentive wait staff.  Watch out for added charges.  We had 4 people and ordered 3 appetizers and 4 dinners.  We were charged $2 each for shared plates for the appetizers.  In addition, we brought a birthday cake and were charged another $2 each  cake plates.  Total charge for 8 plates was $16.
